"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.3.12\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.3.12</span> 标题：补丁（patch）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：תלא</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：tala’（动词）)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:5\">JOS 9:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἐπίβλημα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：epiblēma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:16\">MAT 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:21\">MRK 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:36\">LUK 5:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:36\">LUK 5:36</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：πλήρωμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：plērōma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:16\">MAT 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:21\">MRK 2:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ῥάκος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：rhakos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:16\">MAT 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:21\">MRK 2:21</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/UBS-0012_patches_sewn.png\" alt=\"缝在旧水皮上的补丁\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">缝在旧水皮上的补丁 (Gary Todd, Israel Museum, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>补丁是缝在衣服或鞋子上的一块布或皮革，用来修补破洞或裂口。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:5\">JOS 9:5</a> ：基遍使者的鞋子被多次“补过”，即用皮革修补。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:16\">MAT 9:16</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:21\">MRK 2:21</a> ：“没有人用新布块补缀旧衣服”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直译），这话在某些社会中是荒谬的或难以置信的，因为人们通常就是用新布块来缝补旧衣服，有时甚至会补到难以分辨最初布料的地步。然而，常译为“新布”的希腊文短语<em>rhakous agnafou</em> 的字面意思是“没有缩水的布”，意即还没有洗过，因此还没有缩水的布（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Dutch Common Language Version\">DUCL</abbr> “还没有缩水的补丁”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr> 的译法类似）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
